      "author": "hikosalaidarkcommit",
      "description": "### Plugin Renamed\n- **Plugin renamed to 'Confluence Page Import'**: the previous name 'Confluence Import' collided with an existing plugin in the Obsidian Community Plugins directory. The unique ID `confluence-import` remains unchanged.\n\n### Features\n- **Strict one-way pull**: Import Confluence pages into Obsidian without ever modifying the remote source.\n- **Read-only Diff Preview**: Review exactly what differs between local and remote before applying any changes.\n- **External edit protection**: Aborts pull if the local note changed while the preview window was open to prevent clobbering.\n- **Credential safety**: Strict origin validation (host + protocol) and Unicode-safe Cloud auth.\n\n### Requirements\n- Obsidian 1.4.4 or newer.\n- Desktop version of Obsidian.",
